comment:
Sometimes I'm grateful for the fact that I'm a coldhearted piece of shit because I can get myself out of these kinds of situations. I'm grateful in these situations because I can slip out of the vices of manipulative bitches. However I do have a fragile body, and it's not the best for me when people hit me.
When people attack me verbally, I first make it so it's a neutral matter, first de-escalating the problem then setting up a situation where I can get away from the attacker when they're not on their high guard.
It's kind of a low trick, but as long as it's used in a good way and not as a way the attacker to destroy the defending one.

Basically:
1. Let them attack you but don't show emotion. Make them go out of control and state it's not your problem because it's something they started in the first place anyway.
2. Pick apart their flawed arguments that you heard all at the same time and show all the contradictions and double standards.
3. When they're on the defensive, they will likely subtly admit to what they did while trying to deny the fact that they did it. When they do, interrupt them and leave them to their own shit.
4. If they try to latch onto your life, THEY'RE now on the low end of the relationship and YOU can now turn them over to the others in both your and their life. If they don't try to stay with you, it's your gain anyway.

comment: Big fan, great video as always!  So please don't get me wrong on this criticism, but I have to point out a few things.  Ok, so terms like Gaslighting (coined because it is the plot of an old movie), Stonewalling, etc aren't traits exclusively performed by partners in a relationship, but actually part of a very huge spectrum of human behavior and not an indication of a specific motivation.  I think it becomes trendy to reuse the terminology that is meant for Counseling and Psychology in personal mental health care work.  It isn't meant to be used as a general education tool.  Anyone who studies or practices psychology can explain these are colloquial uses that are meant to illustrate abstract concepts that particular Psych subscribes to easily to a lay person.  Patients should definitely not be using their experience to diagnose the public, it won't work.  I am not saying YOU are mislabeling or incorrect here, but in general I am over hearing and seeing these terms trending ask fucking Memes and Social Media posts with no justification.  It has the air of pretentiousness and it reminds me of the stereotype of Prisoners coming out with Religion and preaching at all the lowlifes that surrounded them before and don't get the irony or self awareness that Religion and the morals taught by religions are new concepts that nobody knows about, but also that lack of religion is extremely inconsequential to their negative fates.  Obviously there are people who have devout beliefs and still go to prison anyway.  Just like there are people with Psychology Education who still experience Mental Health issues, encounter relations with Mental Health issues in their personal life and their knowledge isn't truly helpful because Pschology is based on a lot of loose concepts that encompass studies of other Social Sciences.  Stonewalling and Gaslighting are tactics in Politics, Debate, Business, Negotiations, Economics, Foreign Relations and Policy, Journalism, War, Gaming, Competitive Events, and in general a trick people pull from their sleeve when they are accomplished at successfully using it to their advantage.  Stonewalling requires a person in a  position of power, strength, they usually have a tactical advantage like huge numbers,  allies, fortified secure hold on a vital stronghold position and can basically sustain acceptable losses that lull the opponent into a Stalemate/Forefeit/Truce because their resources are depleted and the battle is fruitless to continue.  Stonewalling doesn't mean you are right or wrong in the argument, someone who is right might Stonewall as a response to any other defense mechanism that could be used by their opponent.  And Gaslighting, is not only super rare for anyone to realistically try, logically have the resources and psychological expertise to execute, but mostly it is attributed to so many basic defensive reactions like pure denial, poorly thought out excuses, and explaining or reframing events to keep them out of trouble.  We learn this young and many people revert to it because right or wrong, justified or not it is obvious when someone is upset about the possibility you did something they already prejudged as a bad act, then admitting wrong doing, active participation, etc mostly results in punishment.  Humans naturally have self preservation and unless really stupid or naive will admit guilt freely unless there is some benefit or compromise to do so.  Throwing every normal condition of behavior as an unmbrella term to work as a catchall like Narcissist.  Except for Clinical Narcissism which may be in a Sociopath Killer, Body Dismorphia, Extreme Body Modifications, Piercings, Tattoos, Plastic Surgeries, Body Building, or any other Extreme Obsession that abstractly distorts their image.  Even extremely Overweight people are Clinical Narcissists, and most functional, "Normal Looking" people with regular Lifestyles are.  Now Narcissism is another general term that has a basic definition and can apply to most human behavior, since one of our main traits is self preservation and self consciousness means we have an Ego and protect it.  That saying that even villains are the heroes in their own stories is so true because of that fact.  So everyone exhibits all characteristics of a Narcissist at some point and making a checklist to try and diagnose random people like a Buzzfeed article is really uneducated and so useless.   Obviously someone who had all the traits all the time is rare and they would be so Anti-Social to the point of only existing in a Niche Subculture that Exploits them or being a Shut in or getting Committed because of an extreme event that affected bystanders.  It is offensive to people with a true disorder, it is like Clean people saying they are OCD, or dumb people or Hyperactive people saying they are ADD/ADHD, or in principle calling someone Retarded or a Schizo even to make fun of them at the expense of true life conditions.  Some people do bad things in relationships and don't have to be disturbed.  In your personal experience they could be, you experienced it not me, so my issue is when it flys around like a Catchphrase to Hashtag on Twitter,  Facebook and IG.
